  [1] You can get some bigger negative numbers =E2=80=94 its net loss for t=
he quarter was $327.6 million =E2=80=94 but those are kind of misleading. V=
irtually all of that loss has to do with changes in value of its *stock*, w=
hich, again, has little to do with its business. The business is basically =
a small website that runs ads and that costs more to maintain than it makes=
 in ad revenue. I have said before that its closest comparable is probably =
a successful but overstaffed Substack newsletter, and those do not get 10-f=
igure valuations.


  [2] More specifically: Rule 415(a)(1)(x) and 415(a)(4) require primary at=
-the-market offerings to be done on Form S-3. The eligibility requirements =
for Form S-3 include that the registrant has been public for at least 12 ca=
lendar months. And the SEC interprets those requirements to mean that a de-=
SPAC company can=E2=80=99t use Form S-3 for 12 months after the de-SPAC mer=
ger. Katten Muchin Rosenman LLP has a good memo explaining the legal requir=
ements for ATMs and ELOCs.


  [3] Actually there are several caps, including (1) the advance can=E2=80=
=99t be bigger than 100% of the average daily trading volume over the last =
five days (the =E2=80=9CMaximum Advance Amount=E2=80=9D) and (2) Yorkville =
can=E2=80=99t own more than 4.99% of the stock (the =E2=80=9COwnership Limi=
tation=E2=80=9D). There is also a cap based on Nasdaq=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9C20=
% rule,=E2=80=9D which says that companies can=E2=80=99t issue more than 20=
% of their stock at below-market prices without shareholder approval; the m=
echanism of this cap is basically that, if the stock falls below $31.73, th=
e number of shares is limited.


  [4] From the agreement: =E2=80=9CEach Advance Notice must include an Adva=
nce Share Estimate, which unless otherwise agreed to by the Investor, shall=
 equal the number of Advance Shares requested in such Advance Notice and mu=
st be accompanied by irrevocable instructions to the Company=E2=80=99s tran=
sfer agent to immediately issue and deliver to the Investor an amount of Co=
mmon Shares equal to the Advance Share Estimate.=E2=80=9D


  [5] That=E2=80=99s just the number of shares outstanding; given warrants,=
 earnouts, etc., the math is more complicated than that, but never mind.


