dHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB30903d68" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Bailey Lipschultz report=
s</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A little-known New Jerse=
y investment manager that focuses on financing micro-cap and small-cap comp=
anies has found its most high-profile deal: Donald Trump=E2=80=99s media st=
artup.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Yorkville Advisors, which operates o=
ut of Mountainside, about an hour=E2=80=99s drive from Wall Street, recentl=
y inked an agreement with Trump Media &amp; Technology Group Corp. that cou=
ld raise $2.5 billion for the former president=E2=80=99s company. The owner=
 of Truth Social registered 38 million shares late Monday as part of the pa=
ct, according to a filing.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The deal is a cl=
assic Yorkville arrangement. It=E2=80=99s set to provide much-needed funds =
to a company that went public by merging with a blank-check vehicle. Yorkvi=
lle has previously backed clients in cash-burning sectors such as electric =
vehicles, and has worked with a handful of high-profile companies whose sto=
ck has fluctuated wildly, such as VinFast Auto Ltd., and even a few like Lo=
rdstown Motors that have crashed.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">As part o=
f the pact, known as a standby equity purchase agreement, Trump Media has t=
he right but not the obligation to sell shares to Yorkville to raise money =
for working capital and general purposes. In return for signing up, Yorkvil=
le gets 200,000 common shares =E2=80=94 worth $7.4 million based on Tuesday=
=E2=80=99s trading, after an 8.5% decline trimmed Trump Media=E2=80=99s wee=
kly gains.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Yorkville has participated in co=
untless deals that involve so-called de-SPACs, where a private firm goes pu=
blic by merging with a special purpose acquisition company.</p></blockquote=
><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One obvious point here is that Yorkville is n=
ot going to=C2=A0<em>invest=C2=A0</em>$2.5 billion in Trump Media.=C2=A0Yor=
kville=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/3=
6091809.196395/aHR0cHM6Ly9maWxlcy5hZHZpc2VyaW5mby5zZWMuZ292L0lBUEQvQ29udGVu=
dC9Db21tb24vY3JkX2lhcGRfQnJvY2h1cmUuYXNweD9CUkNIUl9WUlNOX0lEPTkxODk1OA/607f=
07ceef4b8524a319a23cB47a6171e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscop=
e" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !import=
ant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-=
style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">total assets under management</a> ar=
e about $323 million. Yorkville is in the moving business, not the storage =
business: Any stock that it buys from Trump Media will be sold directly int=
o the market.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here is <a href=3D"https://li=
nk.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/36091809.196395/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmd=
vdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE4NDk2MzUvMDAwMTE0MDM2MTI0MDMzMTcwL255MjAwMz=
E1MDZ4NV80MjRiMy5odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB5448515d" itemprop=3D"StoryL=
ink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; tex=
