<div id=3D"footnote-3" class=3D"footnote-content" style=3D"font-style: ital=
ic;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">[3] Actually there are several caps, including=
 (1) the advance can=E2=80=99t be bigger than 100% of the average daily tra=
ding volume over the last five days (the =E2=80=9CMaximum Advance Amount=E2=
=80=9D) and (2) Yorkville can=E2=80=99t own more than 4.99% of the stock (t=
he =E2=80=9COwnership Limitation=E2=80=9D). There is also a cap based on Na=
sdaq=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9C20% rule,=E2=80=9D which says that companies can=E2=
=80=99t issue more than 20% of their stock at below-market prices without s=
hareholder approval; the mechanism of this cap is basically that, if the st=
ock falls below $31.73, the number of shares is limited.</p>
</div>
<div id=3D"footnote-4" class=3D"footnote-content" style=3D"font-style: ital=
